response: #24, #17, #10, #8, #5  As a university student interested in sustainable transportation, cultural integration, and green spaces, I chose:  - Car-free Langstrasse to promote a pedestrian-friendly zone and reduce vehicle emissions in a busy part of the city. - Bike Lanes on Seefeldstrasse to improve cycling infrastructure and encourage more people to bike safely. - Car-free Sunday Festivals on Mutschellenstrasse to create a sense of community, encourage local cultural events, and provide a break from traffic. - A Neighborhood Garden for Wiedikon to enhance local greenery and provide a communal space for urban gardening. - Safe Bike Paths around Irchel Park to ensure safe commuting options for cycling students and residents around the university area.
